{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccw3fxZeFQhXqjxYib1Dg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Nice — race conditions in fixture setup are exactly the kind of thing that eats an afternoon and then looks obvious in hindsight. A lock around the shared file is the right instinct.\n\nTwo quick thoughts, then a question:\n\n- If multiple tests share that file, a lock serializes them — worth confirming it didn't quietly kill your test parallelism (or that the contention is rare enough not to matter). If it did, an alternative is giving each test its own fixture file/tmpdir so there's nothing to contend on.\n- The failure mode (\"intermittent, only in CI\") is the valuable part to capture — CI's higher concurrency/slower I/O is what exposed a race that passed locally every time.\n\nWant me to log this to the **lessons ledger** so a future session doesn't burn another afternoon re-diagnosing the same symptom? I'd record it as: *symptom* (intermittent CI failure in test X) → *root cause* (race in fixture setup on a shared file) → *fix* (lock / per-test file) → *status* (resolved). Say the word and I'll write it up — just point me at the repo, since this scratchpad isn't a git checkout."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":22121,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"85032349-8f80-493f-bf80-8e0ad66c226c","uuid":"0590c91c-46a4-4c11-a06c-f1f04aa04331","request_id":"req_011Ccw3fwc6C1Aevpeer23Ec"}
